		"type":"trait monstrueux",
		"livre":"cdx",
		"fr":{
			"description":"La morsure, la piqure ou les griffes de la créature ont un effet paralysant. Au mieux la victime est étourdie par le venin, au pire elle est totalement invalide et sans défense face aux attaques qu'elle subit. L'effet reste actif tant que personne n'administre à la victime un antidote tout en réussissant un test d'Astuce.",
			"novice":"I. Passive. Pour chaque attaque causant des dégâts, la victime effectue un test de Force. S'il est réussi, elle est seulement étourdie et a deux chances d'échouer à toutes ses Actions et Réactions durant un tour. Si le test échoue, la victime peut uniquement faire des Réactions durant un tour, avec, pour chacune, deux chances d'échouer.",
			"adepte":"II. Passive. Similaire à I, mais si la victime échoue au test, elle peut uniquement faire des Réactions durant 1D4 tours, pour chacune, avec deux chances d'échouer.",
			"maitre":"III. Passive. La victime doit réussir un test de [Force -5]. Si le test est réussi, la victime peut uniquement faire des Réactions durant 1D4 tours, pour chacune, avec deux chances d'échouer. Si le test échoue, la victime est totalement paralysée pour 1D8 tours.",
			"nom":"Venin Paralysant"
		},
		"en_31":{
			"novice":"I Action: Passive. For each attack that deals damage, the victim makes a Strong test. If the test is successful, the victim is dazed and has second chance to fail on all success tests and reactive actions for one turn; if the test fails, the victim can only perform reactive actions, with second chance to fail.",
			"adepte":"II Action: Passive. As I, but if the victim fails the test, it can only perform reactive actions with second chance to fail for the next 1D4 turns.",
			"maitre":"III Action: Passive. The target must pass a [Strong -5] test. If the test is successful, the victim can only perform reactive actions with second chance to fail for the next 1D4 turns; if the test fails, the victim is completely paralyzed for 1D8 turns."
		},
		"en":{
			"description":"The creature's claws, venomous bite or stinger has a paralyzing effect. At best, the victim is dazed by the venom; at worst, it is completely incapacitated and unable to protect itself from incoming attacks. The effect remains active until someone administers an antidote to the victim and passes a Cunning test.",
			"novice":"I Action: Passive. For each attack that deals damage, the victim makes a Strong test. If the test is successful, the victim is dazed and has two chances to fail all success tests and reactive actions for one turn; if the test fails, the victim can only perform reactive actions, with two chances to fail.",
			"adepte":"II Action: Passive. As I, but if the victim fails the test, it can only perform reactive actions for the next 1D4 turns, with two chances to fail.",
			"maitre":"III Action: Passive. The target must pass a [Strong −5] test. If the test is successful, the victim can only perform reactive actions for the next 1D4 turns, with two chances to fail; if the test fails, the victim is completely paralyzed for 1D8 turns.",
			"nom":"Paralyzing Venom"
		}
	},
	{
